==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deceptive
<hw>De*cep"tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧ceptif</ets>. See <er>Deceive</er>.]</ety> <def>Tending to
deceive; having power to mislead, or impress with false opinions;
<as>as, a <ex>deceptive</ex> countenance or appearance</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Language altogether <qex>deceptive</qex>, and hiding the deeper
reality from our eyes.</q> <rj><qau>Trench.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Deceptive cadence</b></col> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>, <cd>a
cadence on the subdominant, or in some foreign key, postponing the final
close.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deceptively</ent>⟦br⟧
